col_li.paragraphs:
 For $a, b, c, d \in \mathbb{Z}$, $b, d \neq 0$, we have:
\begin{multline*}
\phi(a/b + c/d) = \phi((ad + bc)/(bd)) = [(ad + bc, bd)]\\
= [(a, b)] + [(c, d)] = \phi(a/b) + \phi(c/d)
\end{multline*}

 For $a, b, c, d \in \mathbb{Z}$, $b, d \neq 0$, we have:
\begin{multline*}
\phi((a/b)(c/d)) = \phi((ac)/(bd)) = [(ac, bd)]\\
= [(a, b)]\cdot[(c, d)] = \phi(a/b)\phi(c/d)
\end{multline*}
